six. Use of cookies and similar technologies

6.1. To ensure that your website is up and running with a simpler experience, we call it a small data file of cookies stored on your computer or mobile device. Cookies usually contain an identifier, website name, and some numbers and characters. The full-screen page turning clock can only read cookies recipes provided by Perfect.

6.2. With the help of cookies, you can store some personal preference data. The next time you visit again, we will display the information you need; or the cookies file that will be used by the full-screen page turning clock to determine your source site, so that the full-screen page turning clock can track the performance of the full-screen page turning clock.

6.3. You can manage your cookies according to your preferences, and you can also clear all cookies saved on your computer. Most web browsers must have the ability to block cookies. However, if you do this, you will need to change user settings each time you visit our website. For more information on how to change browser settings, please visit the relevant settings page of the browser you are using.

6.4. In addition to cookies, we can also use other similar technologies, such as web beacons and pixel tags on our website. For example, the email we send you may contain content that links to our website. If you click on a link, we will track clicks to help us understand your product or service preferences so that we can proactively improve customer service. experience. Web beacons are usually transparent images embedded in websites or emails. With the pixel tag in the email, we can tell if the email is open. If you do not want your activity to be tracked by doing so, you can unsubscribe from our mailing list at any time.

Seven, the security of user information

7.1. The full screen page turning clock takes your information security very seriously. We strive to protect user information with a variety of reasonable physical, electronic and administrative security measures. Prevent unauthorized access, public disclosure, use, modification, damage or loss of user information. We use encryption to improve user information security; we use trusted protection mechanisms to protect our users from malicious attacks; we deploy access control mechanisms to ensure that only authorized personnel can access user information; we will host Security and privacy protection training courses to raise employees' awareness of the importance of protecting user information.

7.2. We will take reasonable and practical steps to avoid irrelevant collection of user information. We will only retain time for the purposes described in this policy, unless required by law or allow extension of your user information. After the retention period of the above user information has passed, we will delete or hide your personal information.

7.3. Please use a complex password to help us keep your account safe. We will do our best to protect the security of any information you send to us. If our physical, technical or management protection facilities are damaged, resulting in unauthorized access, public disclosure, alteration or destruction of information, resulting in damage to your legal rights and interests, we will bear the corresponding legal responsibility.

7.4. In the case of unfortunate user information security incidents (leakage, loss, etc.), we will promptly notify you in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations: basic conditions and possible impacts of security incidents, disposal measures, we take or will take you You can take preventive measures and risk reduction recommendations to remedy you, and we will notify you of the incident as soon as possible through email, letter, phone, push notification, etc. When it is difficult to notify the user by one of the information subjects, we will Notice in a reasonable and effective way.

7.5. At the same time, we will deal with user information security incidents reported in accordance with the requirements of regulatory authorities.

7.6. User information collected in the territory of the People's Republic of China by our specialty stores in China. If we transmit personal information overseas for business needs in accordance with applicable laws, we will obtain your consent in advance and notify you. The purpose of exporting user information, recipients, security measures, security risks, etc.

